DIAGNOSIS: Outer­ocular spines triangular; two hepatic anterolateral spines present; anterior gastric spine present (except in 

B. liberata

). Distal peduncular segments appearing two­segmented (pseudosegments). Antennular dorsal flagellum with 28–85 articles, ventral flagellum with 10–21 articles. Antennal flagellum with 11–44 articles. Pereopod I dactylus dorsal margin spinose; distodorsal carpal spine present; cutting edge spinose. Pereopods II–IV dactyli with produced, rounded heels.

INCLUDED SPECIES:
B. occidentalis J. W. Randall, 1840
;
B. spinosa (H. Milne Edwards and Lucas, 1841)
;
B. doelloi Schmitt, 1942
;
B. liberata Shen, 1949
.
